                                applying to a master’s program at an Irish university, it is mandatory to possess a
                                relevant honors bachelor’s degree, or an equivalent degree diploma.</span></li>
                          <li class="wow fadeInLeft"><span><img src="images/arrow1.png" style="padding-top:7px; padding-right:10px; padding-left:-10px;">Certain
                                years of work experience is a strict requirement for some courses, such as MBA.</span></li>
                          <li class="wow fadeInLeft"><span><img src="images/arrow1.png" style="padding-top:7px; padding-right:10px; padding-left:-10px;">Students
                                are required to submit official transcripts of the subjects studied and examinations
                                taken at the undergraduate level to prove their eligibility. Most Irish universities
                                refuse to accept photocopies; thus, obtain official duplicate transcripts from the
